<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
    <title>Join the Club — Secret Society of Strangers</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="styles.css" />
  </head>
  <body>
    <%- include('components/nav') %>
    <% if (error) { %>
      <div class="toast toast--error" role="alert"><%= error %></div>
    <% } %>
    <main class="document">
      <div class="crest">
        <div class="crest__mark">SSS</div>
        <h1 class="title">The Knock</h1>
        <p class="subtitle">Speak the word and the door will know you</p>
      </div>

      <div class="divider"></div>

      <p style="line-height: 1.6; opacity: 0.85; margin-bottom: 28px">
      You have crossed the threshold, but the inner rooms remain shut to you. If you carry the word, the society will recognize you as one of its own — though not all words open the same doors. Some are granted membership. Others are granted custody of the records.
      </p>

      <form id="join-form" method="post" action="/join">
        <div class="field">
          <label for="passcode">The word</label>
          <input
            type="password"
            id="passcode"
            name="passcode"
            placeholder="&bull; &bull; &bull; &bull; &bull; &bull; &bull;"
            autocomplete="off"
            required
          />
          <p class="field-error" id="passcode-error">
            The door does not recognize that word.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="seal-button-row">
          <button
            type="submit"
            class="seal-button"
            aria-label="Submit the word"
          >
            Knock
          </button>
        </div>
      </form>

      <p class="footer-note">
        Not yet ready?
        <a href="/" class="text-link">Return to the Common Room</a>
      </p>
    </main>
  </body>
</html>
